# Java Reserved Words (Keywords) with Examples

Java has **53 reserved words (keywords)**. These words have predefined meanings and **cannot be used as identifiers** (variable names, class names, method names, etc.).

---

# 1. Reserved Words for Data Types (8)

These keywords define primitive data types.

| Keyword | Description      | Example                          |
| ------- | ---------------- | -------------------------------- |
| byte    | 8-bit integer    | `byte age = 25;`                 |
| short   | 16-bit integer   | `short marks = 100;`             |
| int     | 32-bit integer   | `int salary = 50000;`            |
| long    | 64-bit integer   | `long population = 8000000000L;` |
| float   | Single precision | `float price = 99.5f;`           |
| double  | Double precision | `double pi = 3.14159;`           |
| char    | Single character | `char grade = 'A';`              |
| boolean | true/false       | `boolean active = true;`         |

### Example

```java
public class DataTypesExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        byte age = 25;
        short marks = 95;
        int salary = 50000;
        long mobile = 9876543210L;
        float price = 99.99f;
        double pi = 3.14159;
        char grade = 'A';
        boolean isActive = true;

        System.out.println(age);
        System.out.println(isActive);
    }
}
```

