# 2. Reserved Words for Flow Control (11)

Used to control the execution flow.

| Keyword  | Example                |
| -------- | ---------------------- |
| if       | `if(age > 18)`         |
| else     | `else {}`              |
| switch   | `switch(choice)`       |
| case     | `case 1:`              |
| default  | `default:`             |
| for      | `for(int i=0;i<5;i++)` |
| do       | `do{ }while();`        |
| while    | `while(i<5)`           |
| break    | `break;`               |
| continue | `continue;`            |
| return   | `return value;`        |

### Example

```java
public class FlowExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        int age = 20;

        if(age >= 18)
            System.out.println("Eligible");
        else
            System.out.println("Not Eligible");

        for(int i=1;i<=3;i++) {
            System.out.println(i);
        }
    }
}
```

